title: Compatibility question
message: In Quanta ut1 with 215-0674034 can I put 215-0752007 or any cheaper chip then 4034?

title: Compatibility question
message: Nope, must be this exact one. 4034 are <$30 so no idea how much cheaper you want this to become. Also replace PQ41 while you are at this if it is a FD6690.

title: Compatibility question
message: I was told that 215-0674042 can bu used instead 215-0674034. Is that true?

title: Compatibility question
message: Is some cases yes. Not sure about UT1, you can try but why waste time?
